{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1774144619167_6nk4v0122lo","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-4.7","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_5a8c94e9780b4e7a825995b4","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/plan.md << 'EOF'\n# Plan for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n1. **Session Binding Service** (NEW)\n   - Manages mapping between Web session IDs and Telegram chat IDs\n   - Provides API for binding/unbinding sessions\n   - Persists binding state to disk\n\n2. **Unified Message Processor** (NEW)\n   - Single entry point for both Web and Telegram messages\n   - Uses `ai-cli-service.js` for execution\n   - Broadcasts events via `realtime-hub.js`\n\n3. **SSE Event Enhancement** (MODIFY)\n   - Extend `realtime-hub.js` to support cross-channel publishing\n   - Add new event types: `telegram_message`, `user_message`\n\n4. **Telegram Bot Integration** (MODIFY)\n   - Publish messages to `realtime-hub.js` when processing\n   - Listen for Web-originated messages and forward to user\n\n## Data Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐              ┌─────────────────────┐\n│ Web Client  │              │  Telegram Bot       │\n└──────┬──────┘              └──────────┬──────────┘\n       │                                │\n       │ POST /api/chat                 │ on('text')\n       │ (with telegramChatId if bound) │\n       ▼                                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         Session Binding Service (session-bind.js)    │\n│  webSessionId <-> telegramChatId mapping             │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│      Unified Message Processor (message-router.js)   │\n│  - Uses executeAiCli() for all channels             │\n│  - Appends to sessionStore with unified sessionKey  │\n│  - Publishes events to realtimeHub                 │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n         ┌────────────────────────┐\n         │  executeAiCli()        │\n         │  (ai-cli-service.js)   │\n         └────────┬───────────────┘\n                  │\n                  ▼\n         ┌────────────────────────┐\n         │  publish()             │\n         │  realtimeHub           │\n         └───────┬────────────────┘\n                 │\n    ┌────────────┴────────────┐\n    ▼                         ▼\n┌──────────┐           ┌──────────┐\n│ Web SSE  │           │ Telegram │\n│ Events   │           │ Forward  │\n└──────────┘           └──────────┘\n```\n\n## Session Key Strategy\n\n- **Unified sessionKey**: `telegram:{chatId}`\n- **Web session binding**: When Web client provides `telegramChatId`, use that sessionKey\n- **Fallback**: If no binding, create isolated `web:{webSessionId}` session (not synced)\n\n## Files to Create\n\n1. `src/services/session-bind.js` - Session binding service\n2. `src/services/message-router.js` - Unified message processor\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n1. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add binding endpoint, use message-router\n2. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Publish to realtimeHub, listen for Web messages\n3. `src/services/index.js` - Export new services\n4. `src/services/chat-service.js` - Keep for backwards compatibility but deprecate\n\n## Testing Approach\n\n1. Unit tests for session-binding logic\n2. Integration tests for Web -> Telegram sync\n3. Integration tests for Telegram -> Web sync\n4. Test offline reconnection scenario\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] T1.1 Create `src/services/session-bind.js` with:\n  - `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)` function\n  - `unbindSession(webSessionId)` function\n  - `getBoundChatId(webSessionId)` function\n  - `getBoundWebSessions(telegramChatId)` function\n  - Persistence to JSON file in `config.sessionPersistenceDir`\n\n- [ ] T1.2 Create unit tests for `session-bind.js`\n\n- [ ] T1.3 Create `src/services/message-router.js` with:\n  - `processMessage({ channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId, hooks })`\n  - Uses `executeAiCli()` for execution\n  - Appends to sessionStore\n  - Publishes events to realtimeHub for both channels\n\n- [ ] T1.4 Create unit tests for `message-router.js`\n\n### Phase 2: Web Integration\n\n- [ ] T2.1 Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js`:\n  - Add POST `/api/bind` endpoint: `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)`\n  - Add POST `/api/unbind` endpoint\n  - Add GET `/api/bindings` endpoint to get current binding\n  - Replace `chatWithSession()` with `message-router.processMessage()`\n  - Pass `telegramChatId` if bound\n\n- [ ] T2.2 Create integration tests for binding endpoints\n\n- [ ] T2.3 Test Web -> Telegram message sync\n\n### Phase 3: Telegram Integration\n\n- [ ] T3.1 Modify `src/bot/telegram.js`:\n  - Import `realtimeHub` and `message-router`\n  - When processing text messages, publish `user_message` event with message text\n  - When AI replies, publish `assistant_message` event with reply\n  - Add handler for Web-originated messages (optional: forward to Telegram chat)\n\n- [ ] T3.2 Test Telegram -> Web SSE sync\n\n### Phase 4: Cross-Channel Synchronization\n\n- [ ] T4.1 Extend `src/services/realtime-hub.js`:\n  - Add `broadcastToChannel(channel, event)` for targeted publishing\n  - Add event type for cross-channel sync\n\n- [ ] T4.2 Implement message replay for offline Web clients:\n  - SSE connection catches up with missed messages from sessionStore\n\n- [ ] T4.3 Test bidirectional sync with both clients online\n\n### Phase 5: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] T5.1 Document Web-Telegram binding API\n\n- [ ] T5.2 Add deprecation notice to `src/services/chat-service.js`\n\n- [ ] T5.3 Run full integration test suite\n\n- [ ] T5.4 Update `.prizm-docs/` with new services\nEOF","description":"Write plan.md with implementation tasks"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":57808,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94710a11-4ada-4b2b-b382-cda110153e6d","uuid":"7d656f4a-0e26-4e3a-a652-453c5e9dded5"}
