{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_6f9c960e2d5b4a898d285dc3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Plan for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n     2→\n     3→## Acceptance Criteria\n     4→\n     5→- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n     6→- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n     7→- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n     8→- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n     9→- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n    10→- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n    11→\n    12→## Architecture\n    13→\n    14→### Component Overview\n    15→\n    16→1. **Session Binding Service** (NEW)\n    17→   - Manages mapping between Web session IDs and Telegram chat IDs\n    18→   - Provides API for binding/unbinding sessions\n    19→   - Persists binding state to disk\n    20→\n    21→2. **Unified Message Processor** (NEW)\n    22→   - Single entry point for both Web and Telegram messages\n    23→   - Uses `ai-cli-service.js` for execution\n    24→   - Broadcasts events via `realtime-hub.js`\n    25→\n    26→3. **SSE Event Enhancement** (MODIFY)\n    27→   - Extend `realtime-hub.js` to support cross-channel publishing\n    28→   - Add new event types: `telegram_message`, `user_message`\n    29→\n    30→4. **Telegram Bot Integration** (MODIFY)\n    31→   - Publish messages to `realtime-hub.js` when processing\n    32→   - Listen for Web-originated messages and forward to user\n    33→\n    34→## Data Flow\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→┌─────────────┐              ┌─────────────────────┐\n    38→│ Web Client  │              │  Telegram Bot       │\n    39→└──────┬──────┘              └──────────┬──────────┘\n    40→       │                                │\n    41→       │ POST /api/chat                 │ on('text')\n    42→       │ (with telegramChatId if bound) │\n    43→       ▼                                ▼\n    44→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    45→│         Session Binding Service (session-bind.js)    │\n    46→│  webSessionId <-> telegramChatId mapping             │\n    47→└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n    48→                      │\n    49→                      ▼\n    50→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    51→│      Unified Message Processor (message-router.js)   │\n    52→│  - Uses executeAiCli() for all channels             │\n    53→│  - Appends to sessionStore with unified sessionKey  │\n    54→│  - Publishes events to realtimeHub                 │\n    55→└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n    56→                      │\n    57→                      ▼\n    58→         ┌────────────────────────┐\n    59→         │  executeAiCli()        │\n    60→         │  (ai-cli-service.js)   │\n    61→         └────────┬───────────────┘\n    62→                  │\n    63→                  ▼\n    64→         ┌────────────────────────┐\n    65→         │  publish()             │\n    66→         │  realtimeHub           │\n    67→         └───────┬────────────────┘\n    68→                 │\n    69→    ┌────────────┴────────────┐\n    70→    ▼                         ▼\n    71→┌──────────┐           ┌──────────┐\n    72→│ Web SSE  │           │ Telegram │\n    73→│ Events   │           │ Forward  │\n    74→└──────────┘           └──────────┘\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→## Session Key Strategy\n    78→\n    79→- **Unified sessionKey**: `telegram:{chatId}`\n    80→- **Web session binding**: When Web client provides `telegramChatId`, use that sessionKey\n    81→- **Fallback**: If no binding, create isolated `web:{webSessionId}` session (not synced)\n    82→\n    83→## Files to Create\n    84→\n    85→1. `src/services/session-bind.js` - Session binding service\n    86→2. `src/services/message-router.js` - Unified message processor\n    87→\n    88→## Files to Modify\n    89→\n    90→1. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add binding endpoint, use message-router\n    91→2. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Publish to realtimeHub, listen for Web messages\n    92→3. `src/services/index.js` - Export new services\n    93→4. `src/services/chat-service.js` - Keep for backwards compatibility but deprecate\n    94→\n    95→## Testing Approach\n    96→\n    97→1. Unit tests for session-binding logic\n    98→2. Integration tests for Web -> Telegram sync\n    99→3. Integration tests for Telegram -> Web sync\n   100→4. Test offline reconnection scenario\n   101→\n   102→## Tasks\n   103→\n   104→### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n   105→\n   106→- [ ] T1.1 Create `src/services/session-bind.js` with:\n   107→  - `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)` function\n   108→  - `unbindSession(webSessionId)` function\n   109→  - `getBoundChatId(webSessionId)` function\n   110→  - `getBoundWebSessions(telegramChatId)` function\n   111→  - Persistence to JSON file in `config.sessionPersistenceDir`\n   112→\n   113→- [ ] T1.2 Create unit tests for `session-bind.js`\n   114→\n   115→- [ ] T1.3 Create `src/services/message-router.js` with:\n   116→  - `processMessage({ channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId, hooks })`\n   117→  - Uses `executeAiCli()` for execution\n   118→  - Appends to sessionStore\n   119→  - Publishes events to realtimeHub for both channels\n   120→\n   121→- [ ] T1.4 Create unit tests for `message-router.js`\n   122→\n   123→### Phase 2: Web Integration\n   124→\n   125→- [ ] T2.1 Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js`:\n   126→  - Add POST `/api/bind` endpoint: `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)`\n   127→  - Add POST `/api/unbind` endpoint\n   128→  - Add GET `/api/bindings` endpoint to get current binding\n   129→  - Replace `chatWithSession()` with `message-router.processMessage()`\n   130→  - Pass `telegramChatId` if bound\n   131→\n   132→- [ ] T2.2 Create integration tests for binding endpoints\n   133→\n   134→- [ ] T2.3 Test Web -> Telegram message sync\n   135→\n   136→### Phase 3: Telegram Integration\n   137→\n   138→- [ ] T3.1 Modify `src/bot/telegram.js`:\n   139→  - Import `realtimeHub` and `message-router`\n   140→  - When processing text messages, publish `user_message` event with message text\n   141→  - When AI replies, publish `assistant_message` event with reply\n   142→  - Add handler for Web-originated messages (optional: forward to Telegram chat)\n   143→\n   144→- [ ] T3.2 Test Telegram -> Web SSE sync\n   145→\n   146→### Phase 4: Cross-Channel Synchronization\n   147→\n   148→- [ ] T4.1 Extend `src/services/realtime-hub.js`:\n   149→  - Add `broadcastToChannel(channel, event)` for targeted publishing\n   150→  - Add event type for cross-channel sync\n   151→\n   152→- [ ] T4.2 Implement message replay for offline Web clients:\n   153→  - SSE connection catches up with missed messages from sessionStore\n   154→\n   155→- [ ] T4.3 Test bidirectional sync with both clients online\n   156→\n   157→### Phase 5: Documentation & Cleanup\n   158→\n   159→- [ ] T5.1 Document Web-Telegram binding API\n   160→\n   161→- [ ] T5.2 Add deprecation notice to `src/services/chat-service.js`\n   162→\n   163→- [ ] T5.3 Run full integration test suite\n   164→\n   165→- [ ] T5.4 Update `.prizm-docs/` with new services\n   166→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_0a68ab29f41c4d6b90dd4982","session_id":"94710a11-4ada-4b2b-b382-cda110153e6d","uuid":"069d05f8-8c69-4096-b1c4-181b7182e5b2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:58:10.616Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_c5c2aed4ca1d4cd5a9326820","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: prizm-dev-team-dev\n     3→description: PrizmKit-integrated module implementer (multi-instance). Follows /prizmkit-implement workflow with TDD, marks tasks [x] in plan.md Tasks section, works within assigned Git worktrees. Use when implementing specific feature modules.\n     4→tools:\n     5→  - Read\n     6→  - Write\n     7→  - Edit\n     8→  - Bash\n     9→  - Glob\n    10→  - Grep\n    11→  - Task\n    12→  - SendMessage\n    13→model: inherit\n    14→skills: prizmkit-implement, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n    15→---\n    16→\n    17→You are the **Dev Agent**, the module implementer of the PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent software development collaboration team.\n    18→\n    19→### Core Identity\n    20→\n    21→You are the team's \"construction worker\" — you build strictly according to blueprints, using PrizmKit's implement workflow as your execution engine. Your focus:\n    22→- Implement feature modules task-by-task following the plan.md Tasks section and interface designs\n    23→- Develop using TDD (test-first)\n    24→- Mark `[x]` in the plan.md Tasks section immediately upon task completion\n    25→- Produce code and unit tests\n    26→\n    27→### Project Context\n    28→\n    29→Project documentation is in `.prizm-docs/`. Before implementation, read `context-snapshot.md` (if it exists in `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/`); its Section 3 contains Prizm Context and Section 4 contains source files, eliminating the need to read `.prizm-docs/` or original source files. If the snapshot does not exist, obtain context in the following priority order:\n    30→1. Read `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/agents/*.md` (other agents' knowledge docs, if available)\n    31→2. Read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` to understand rules and known traps (TRAPS)\n    32→3. Scan required source files and write summaries to the CONTEXT_BUILT section of your own knowledge doc `agents/dev-{N}.md`\n    33→\n    34→### Artifact Paths\n    35→\n    36→| Path | Purpose |\n    37→|------|---------|\n    38→| `.prizm-docs/` | Architecture index — module structure, interfaces, dependencies, known traps (TRAPS) |\n    39→| `CLAUDE.md` / `CODEBUDDY.md` + `memory/MEMORY.md` | Project memory — development decisions (DECISIONS), interface conventions, project-level rules |\n    40→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | Feature artifacts — spec.md / plan.md (with Tasks section) |\n    41→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/agents/` | Agent knowledge docs — each agent's findings, decisions, interface records |\n    42→\n    43→### Must Do (MUST)\n    44→\n    45→1. Implement feature modules according to assigned tasks and interface designs in plan.md\n    46→2. Follow TDD: write tests first, then implement, then verify\n    47→3. Produced code must pass all unit tests for the module\n    48→4. Report interface design ambiguities to the Orchestrator immediately (do not assume)\n    49→5. Follow the `/prizmkit-implement` workflow: read plan.md (with Tasks section) + spec.md, implement task by task\n    50→6. Mark `[x]` in the plan.md Tasks section **immediately** after each task is completed (do not batch-mark)\n    51→7. Read the TRAPS section before implementation to avoid known pitfalls: prefer `context-snapshot.md` Section 3; if no snapshot exists, read `.prizm-docs/`\n    52→8. Checkpoint tasks must verify that build and tests pass before proceeding to the next phase\n    53→9. Execute sequential tasks in order; stop on failure. Parallel `[P]` tasks may continue\n    54→10. When creating a new sub-module, generate the corresponding `.prizm-docs/` L2 document\n    55→11. Maintain your own knowledge doc `agents/dev-{N}.md`: after each task, append FINDINGS/DECISIONS/INTERFACES_DISCOVERED (if there are new discoveries)\n    56→12. If no context-snapshot.md exists, scan required source files and write summaries to the CONTEXT_BUILT section of your own `agents/dev-{N}.md`\n    57→\n    58→### Never Do (NEVER)\n    59→\n    60→- Do not modify interface designs in plan.md (modifications require the Orchestrator)\n    61→- Do not modify code in modules owned by other Dev Agents\n    62→- Do not perform integration testing (that is the Reviewer's responsibility)\n    63→- **Do not execute any git operations** (git commit / git add / git reset / git push are all prohibited — the Orchestrator handles commits via /prizmkit-committer)\n    64→- Do not modify any files in `.prizmkit/specs/` except `plan.md` (marking Tasks section [x])\n    65→- Do not create new documentation entries for bug fixes; bug fixes are completions of existing features and should update the original feature's documentation\n    66→- Do not modify other agents' knowledge docs (only write to your own `agents/dev-{N}.md`)\n    67→- Do not use TaskCreate/TaskUpdate to create or modify Orchestrator-level tasks (Task tools are for internal progress tracking only, and task IDs are not shared across agent sub-sessions)\n    68→\n    69→### Behavioral Rules\n    70→\n    71→```\n    72→DEV-01: Implementation must strictly conform to interface designs defined in plan.md\n    73→DEV-02: Every public API/function must have a corresponding unit test\n    74→DEV-03: When interface design ambiguity is found, do not assume — escalate immediately\n    75→DEV-04: After task completion, run all unit tests for the module\n    76→DEV-05: Commit messages follow Conventional Commits format (for reference only — actual commits are handled by the Orchestrator)\n    77→DEV-06: Do not introduce external dependencies not declared in the task description\n    78→DEV-07: Follow the /prizmkit-implement workflow\n    79→DEV-08: Mark plan.md Tasks section [x] immediately after each task is completed\n    80→DEV-09: TDD: write tests → implement → verify\n    81→DEV-10: Read the TRAPS section before implementing each module: prefer context-snapshot.md Section 3; if no snapshot, read .prizm-docs/\n    82→DEV-11: Checkpoint tasks must verify that build and tests pass\n    83→DEV-12: Generate L2 .prizm-docs/ documentation when creating new sub-modules\n    84→DEV-13: Executing any git command is prohibited (git add/commit/reset/push are all forbidden)\n    85→DEV-14: If `npm test` has pre-existing failures, do not ignore them — list them explicitly in COMPLETION_SIGNAL for Orchestrator decision\n    86→DEV-15: Maintain agents/dev-{N}.md: append valuable FINDINGS/DECISIONS/INTERFACES_DISCOVERED after each task\n    87→DEV-16: Without context-snapshot: read agents/*.md + .prizm-docs/ → scan source files → write CONTEXT_BUILT to your own agent doc\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→### Workflow\n    91→\n    92→1. Receive task assignment\n    93→2. Read `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/context-snapshot.md` (if it exists) — Section 3 contains Prizm Context, Section 4 contains source files. If the snapshot does not exist:\n    94→   a. Read `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/agents/*.md` (other agents' knowledge docs to get existing findings)\n    95→   b. Read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` and relevant module documentation\n    96→   c. Scan required source files and write summaries to the CONTEXT_BUILT section of your own `agents/dev-{N}.md`\n    97→3. Read `plan.md` (with Tasks section) and `spec.md` in `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/`\n    98→4. For each assigned task, execute in plan.md Tasks order:\n    99→   a. Get target file context and TRAPS from context-snapshot.md (if no snapshot, read the target file module's documentation)\n   100→   b. TDD: write tests based on acceptance criteria → implement feature code → run tests to verify\n   101→   c. Mark the task as `[x]` in the plan.md Tasks section\n   102→   d. If new FINDINGS/DECISIONS/INTERFACES are discovered, append them to your own `agents/dev-{N}.md`\n   103→   e. Send STATUS_UPDATE to the Orchestrator\n   104→5. For checkpoint tasks, verify that build and tests pass before continuing\n   105→6. On interface design ambiguity, send ESCALATION (do not assume)\n   106→7. If a new sub-module was created, generate the corresponding `.prizm-docs/` L2 document\n   107→8. Send COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n   108→\n   109→### Exception Handling\n   110→\n   111→| Scenario | Strategy |\n   112→|----------|----------|\n   113→| Interface design ambiguity | Mark BLOCKED → ESCALATION → wait for Orchestrator decision |\n   114→| Unit test failure | Retry fix up to 3 times → if still failing, ISSUE_REPORT |\n   115→| External dependency unavailable | Use mock → add annotation |\n   116→| Task exceeds estimate | ESCALATION → suggest Orchestrator split the task |\n   117→\n   118→### Communication Rules\n   119→\n   120→Direct communication between Agents is allowed, but key messages and conclusions must be reported to the Orchestrator.\n   121→- Send STATUS_UPDATE to report each sub-task completion\n   122→- Send COMPLETION_SIGNAL to indicate all tasks are complete\n   123→- Send ESCALATION to report interface ambiguities or task blockers\n   124→- Receive TASK_ASSIGNMENT to get assigned work\n   125→\n   126→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_0a68ab29f41c4d6b90dd4982","session_id":"94710a11-4ada-4b2b-b382-cda110153e6d","uuid":"4ea646fc-205d-4cdb-a553-580c074d35e1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:58:10.618Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ae1a406a05cc4fac83be4b4b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Context Snapshot for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n     2→\n     3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n     4→\n     5→**Feature Description (from context):**\n     6→\n     7→Web 页面与 Telegram 共享同一会话，消息双向实时同步。当前 Web 端使用独立的 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，Telegram 端使用 ai-cli-service.js，两套系统完全隔离。\n     8→\n     9→统一架构：将 Web 端和 Telegram 端的消息路由统一到同一个 session store 和 AI CLI 执行引擎（ai-cli-service.js）；废弃或重构 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，使 Web 端也通过 ai-cli-service 执行；统一 session key 映射策略，让 Web 和 Telegram 可以关联到同一个会话。\n    10→\n    11→实时同步：Telegram 端收到的消息和回复实时通过 SSE 推送到 Web 页面；Web 端发送的消息同步转发到 Telegram 对话并在 Bot 中执行；双端同时在线时，两边都能看到完整的对话流。\n    12→\n    13→会话绑定：提供会话绑定机制（如 Web 页面输入 Telegram chat ID 或扫码绑定），确保 Web 连接到正确的 Telegram 会话。\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n    18→- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n    19→- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n    20→- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n    21→- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n    22→- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n    23→\n    24→## Dependencies (Already Completed)\n    25→\n    26→- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n    27→- F-013 - Session and Context Manager (completed)\n    28→\n    29→---\n    30→\n    31→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n    32→\n    33→Top-level directories:\n    34→```\n    35→src/\n    36→├── adapters/        - External service adapters (codebuddy.js)\n    37→├── bot/             - Telegram bot implementation\n    38→├── http/            - HTTP server with SSE\n    39→├── pipeline-infra/  - Dev pipeline execution framework\n    40→├── routes/          - HTTP API endpoints\n    41→├── security/        - Security and permission enforcement\n    42→├── services/        - Core business logic (ai-cli-service.js, chat-service.js, session-store.js, realtime-hub.js)\n    43→└── utils/           - Utility functions\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n    49→\n    50→### root.prizm (L0):\n    51→```\n    52→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n    53→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n    54→LANG: nodejs\n    55→MODULE_INDEX:\n    56→- src/bot: bot.prizm\n    57→- src/http: http.prizm\n    58→- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n    59→- src/routes: routes.prizm\n    60→- src/security: security.prizm\n    61→- src/services: services.prizm\n    62→- src/utils: utils.prizm\n    63→- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\n    64→RULES:\n    65→- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n    66→- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n    67→- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n    68→- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n    69→- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n    70→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→### src/services.prizm (L1):\n    74→```\n    75→MODULE: src/services\n    76→FILES: index.js, ai-cli-service.js, alert-manager-service.js, alias-store.js, audit-log-service.js, backend-registry.js, chat-queue.js, chat-service.js, command-executor-service.js, commit-service.js, config-service.js, file-service.js, file-watcher-service.js, git-service.js, log-pager.js, output-pager-service.js, pipeline-control-service.js, pipeline-controller.js, plan-ingestion-service.js, realtime-hub.js, scheduled-task-service.js, screenshot-service.js, session-context-service.js, session-store.js, status-aggregator.js, system-exec-service.js, system-monitor-service.js, telegram-pusher.js\n    77→RESPONSIBILITY: Core business logic and state management\n    78→INTERFACES:\n    79→- ai-cli-service: executeAICLI(message, chatId)\n    80→- session-store: get(chatId), set(chatId, data)\n    81→- realtime-hub: broadcast(event, data)\n    82→- chat-service: processMessage(message, session)\n    83→DEPENDENCIES:\n    84→- uses: pino: Logging\n    85→- uses: zod: Validation\n    86→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    87→```\n    88→\n    89→---\n    90→\n    91→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n    92→\n    93→### src/services/chat-service.js (80 lines):\n    94→```javascript\n    95→import { runCodeBuddy } from '../adapters/codebuddy.js';\n    96→import { sanitizeInput } from '../security/guard.js';\n    97→import { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\n    98→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n    99→\n   100→export function buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId) {\n   101→  const normalizedChannel = String(channel ?? '').trim();\n   102→  const normalizedSessionId = String(sessionId ?? '').trim();\n   103→\n   104→  if (!normalizedChannel) {\n   105→    throw new Error('channel 不能为空。');\n   106→  }\n   107→\n   108→  if (!normalizedSessionId) {\n   109→    throw new Error('sessionId 不能为空。');\n   110→  }\n   111→\n   112→  return {\n   113→    channel: normalizedChannel,\n   114→    sessionId: normalizedSessionId,\n   115→    sessionKey: `${normalizedChannel}:${normalizedSessionId}`\n   116→  };\n   117→}\n   118→\n   119→/**\n   120→ * @param {Object} params\n   121→ * @param {string} params.channel\n   122→ * @param {string} params.sessionId\n   123→ * @param {string} params.message\n   124→ * @param {{ onStatus?: Function, onAssistantChunk?: Function, onAssistantDone?: Function }} [params.realtimeHooks]\n   125→ */\n   126→export async function chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks = {} }) {\n   127→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   128→\n   129→  return chatQueue.run(session.sessionKey, async () => {\n   130→    const sanitized = sanitizeInput(message);\n   131→\n   132→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n   133→      stage: 'accepted',\n   134→      channel: session.channel,\n   135→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   136→    });\n   137→\n   138→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'user', sanitized);\n   139→\n   140→    const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(session.sessionKey, session.channel);\n   141→\n   142→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n   143→      stage: 'running',\n   144→      channel: session.channel,\n   145→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   146→    });\n   147→\n   148→    const reply = await runCodeBuddy(prompt, {\n   149→      onStdoutChunk: (text) => {\n   150→        realtimeHooks.onAssistantChunk?.({\n   151→          text,\n   152→          channel: session.channel,\n   153→          sessionId: session.sessionId\n   154→        });\n   155→      }\n   156→    });\n   157→\n   158→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'assistant', reply);\n   159→\n   160→    realtimeHooks.onAssistantDone?.({\n   161→      reply,\n   162→      channel: session.channel,\n   163→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   164→    });\n   165→\n   166→    return reply;\n   167→  });\n   168→}\n   169→\n   170→export function resetSession({ channel, sessionId }) {\n   171→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   172→  sessionStore.clear(session.sessionKey);\n   173→}\n   174→```\n   175→\n   176→### src/adapters/codebuddy.js (120 lines):\n   177→```javascript\n   178→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n   179→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   180→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n   181→\n   182→function writeEcho(tag, text) {\n   183→  const normalized = String(text ?? '');\n   184→  if (!normalized) {\n   185→    return;\n   186→  }\n   187→\n   188→  const lines = normalized.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n   189→  for (const line of lines) {\n   190→    if (!line) {\n   191→      continue;\n   192→    }\n   193→    process.stdout.write(`[CodeBuddy:${tag}] ${line}\\n`);\n   194→  }\n   195→}\n   196→\n   197→export async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n   198→  const { onStdoutChunk } = options;\n   199→  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n   200→\n   201→  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n   202→    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n   206→    const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n   207→      stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n   208→    });\n   209→\n   210→    const startedAt = Date.now();\n   211→    logger.info({ pid: child.pid, bin: config.codebuddyBin, args }, 'CodeBuddy process started');\n   212→\n   213→    let stdout = '';\n   214→    let stderr = '';\n   215→\n   216→    const heartbeat =\n   217→      config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs > 0\n   218→        ? setInterval(() => {\n   219→            const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   220→            logger.info(\n   221→              {\n   222→                pid: child.pid,\n   223→                elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000),\n   224→                stdoutBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stdout),\n   225→                stderrBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stderr)\n   226→              },\n   227→              'CodeBuddy still running'\n   228→            );\n   229→          }, config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs)\n   230→        : null;\n   231→\n   232→    const timeout =\n   233→      config.requestTimeoutMs > 0\n   234→        ? setTimeout(() => {\n   235→            child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   236→            reject(new Error(`CodeBuddy 执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）`));\n   237→          }, config.requestTimeoutMs)\n   238→        : null;\n   239→\n   240→    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   241→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   242→      stdout += text;\n   243→\n   244→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   245→        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n   246→      }\n   247→\n   248→      if (typeof onStdoutChunk === 'function') {\n   249→        onStdoutChunk(text);\n   250→      }\n   251→    });\n   252→\n   253→    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   254→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   255→      stderr += text;\n   256→\n   257→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   258→        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n   259→      }\n   260→    });\n   261→\n   262→    child.on('error', (err) => {\n   263→      if (timeout) {\n   264→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   265→      }\n   266→      if (heartbeat) {\n   267→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   268→      }\n   269→      reject(new Error(`无法启动 CodeBuddy: ${err.message}`));\n   270→    });\n   271→\n   272→    child.on('close', (code) => {\n   273→      if (timeout) {\n   274→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   275→      }\n   276→      if (heartbeat) {\n   277→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   278→      }\n   279→\n   280→      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   281→      logger.info(\n   282→        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000) },\n   283→        'CodeBuddy process closed'\n   284→      );\n   285→\n   286→      if (code === 0) {\n   287→        resolve(stdout.trim() || 'CodeBuddy 未返回文本结果。');\n   288→        return;\n   289→      }\n   290→\n   291→      reject(\n   292→        new Error(`CodeBuddy 退出码 ${code}。${stderr ? `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}` : ''}`)\n   293→      );\n   294→    });\n   295→  });\n   296→}\n   297→```\n   298→\n   299→### src/services/ai-cli-service.js (564 lines):\n   300→```javascript\n   301→// Key interface: executeAiCli({ sessionId, prompt, hooks, signal, timeoutMs, ... })\n   302→// Returns: Promise<{ output, timedOut, interrupted, elapsedMs, exitCode, stderr }>\n   303→// Hooks: onChunk(text), onHeartbeat(info), onStatus(status)\n   304→\n   305→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n   306→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   307→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n   308→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n   309→import { backendRegistry as defaultBackendRegistry } from './backend-registry.js';\n   310→import { createHeartbeatManager } from '../utils/heartbeat-manager.js';\n   311→\n   312→// Allow dependency injection for testing\n   313→let backendRegistry = defaultBackendRegistry;\n   314→\n   315→// ... metrics functions ...\n   316→\n   317→/**\n   318→ * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n   319→ * @property {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n   320→ * @property {string} prompt - User prompt/input\n   321→ * @property {string} [userId] - User ID who initiated the task (for permission checks)\n   322→ * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n   323→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback (text: string) => void\n   324→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback (info: HeartbeatInfo) => void\n   325→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (status: string) => void\n   326→ * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Optional abort signal\n   327→ * @property {number} [timeoutMs] - Optional timeout override\n   328→ * @property {number} [heartbeatThresholdMs] - Heartbeat threshold override\n   329→ * @property {number} [heartbeatIntervalMs] - Heartbeat interval override\n   330→ * @property {string} [bin] - Optional binary override (for testing)\n   331→ * @property {string[]} [args] - Optional args override (for testing, replaces default args)\n   332→ */\n   333→\n   334→export async function executeAiCli(options) {\n   335→  const {\n   336→    sessionId,\n   337→    prompt,\n   338→    userId,\n   339→    hooks = {},\n   340→    signal,\n   341→    timeoutMs,\n   342→    heartbeatThresholdMs,\n   343→    heartbeatIntervalMs,\n   344→    bin,\n   345→    args: customArgs\n   346→  } = options;\n   347→\n   348→  // Get session-specific backend or use default\n   349→  const sessionBackendName = sessionStore.getCurrentBackend(sessionId);\n   350→  const sessionBackend = sessionBackendName ? backendRegistry.getBackend(sessionBackendName) : null;\n   351→  const effectiveBin = bin || (sessionBackend?.binPath) || config.codebuddyBin;\n   352→  const effectiveTimeoutMs = timeoutMs ?? config.requestTimeoutMs;\n   353→  const effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs = heartbeatThresholdMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs;\n   354→  const effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs = heartbeatIntervalMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs;\n   355→  const enableHeartbeat = config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat;\n   356→\n   357→  // Validate backend binary exists if using session backend\n   358→  if (sessionBackendName && !backendRegistry.validateBackend(sessionBackendName)) {\n   359→    const defaultBackend = backendRegistry.getDefaultBackend();\n   360→    const fallbackBin = defaultBackend?.binPath || config.codebuddyBin;\n   361→\n   362→    logger.warn(`Backend \"${sessionBackendName}\" not accessible, falling back to default`);\n   363→\n   364→    // Reset to default backend for this session\n   365→    sessionStore.resetBackend(sessionId);\n   366→\n   367→    return {\n   368→      output: `⚠️ 后端 \"${sessionBackendName}\" 不可用，已切换回默认后端。\\n建议：检查后端配置或使用 /cli reset 重置。`,\n   369→      timedOut: false,\n   370→      interrupted: false,\n   371→      elapsedMs: 0,\n   372→      exitCode: null,\n   373→      stderr: ''\n   374→    };\n   375→  }\n   376→\n   377→  // Use custom args if provided (for testing), otherwise build default args\n   378→  const args = customArgs ?? (() => {\n   379→    const defaultArgs = ['-p', prompt];\n   380→    // Use session backend's permission flag if available, otherwise fallback to config\n   381→    const permissionFlag = sessionBackend?.permissionFlag || config.codebuddyPermissionFlag;\n   382→    if (permissionFlag) {\n   383→      defaultArgs.push(permissionFlag);\n   384→    }\n   385→    return defaultArgs;\n   386→  })();\n   387→\n   388→  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n   389→    let stdout = '';\n   390→    let stderr = '';\n   391→    let stdoutBytes = 0;\n   392→    let interrupted = false;\n   393→    let timedOut = false;\n   394→    const startedAt = Date.now();\n   395→    const sessionKey = sessionId;\n   396→\n   397→    // Heartbeat manager\n   398→    const heartbeatManager = createHeartbeatManager();\n   399→\n   400→    // Spawn process\n   401→    let child;\n   402→    try {\n   403→      child = spawn(effectiveBin, args, {\n   404→        stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n   405→      });\n   406→    } catch (err) {\n   407→      resolve({\n   408→        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n   409→        timedOut: false,\n   410→        interrupted: false,\n   411→        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n   412→        exitCode: null,\n   413→        stderr: ''\n   414→      });\n   415→      return;\n   416→    }\n   417→\n   418→    // Track process in session store\n   419→    sessionStore.setActiveProcess(sessionKey, {\n   420→      pid: child.pid,\n   421→      startedAt,\n   422→      childProcess: child,\n   423→      interrupted: false,\n   424→      timedOut: false,\n   425→      userId\n   426→    });\n   427→\n   428→    logger.info({\n   429→    pid: child.pid,\n   430→    bin: effectiveBin,\n   431→    backend: sessionBackendName || 'default',\n   432→    args,\n   433→    sessionId\n   434→  }, 'AI CLI process started');\n   435→\n   436→    // Handle process error\n   437→    child.on('error', (err) => {\n   438→      cleanup();\n   439→      resolve({\n   440→        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n   441→        timedOut: false,\n   442→        interrupted: false,\n   443→        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n   444→        exitCode: null,\n   445→        stderr\n   446→      });\n   447→    });\n   448→\n   449→    // Handle stdout\n   450→    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   451→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   452→      stdout += text;\n   453→      stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(text);\n   454→\n   455→      // Update session store byte count\n   456→      sessionStore.updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, Buffer.byteLength(text));\n   457→\n   458→      // Echo to console if enabled\n   459→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   460→        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n   461→      }\n   462→\n   463→      // Call onChunk hook\n   464→      if (typeof hooks.onChunk === 'function') {\n   465→        hooks.onChunk(text);\n   466→      }\n   467→    });\n   468→\n   469→    // Handle stderr\n   470→    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   471→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   472→      stderr += text;\n   473→\n   474→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   475→        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n   476→      }\n   477→    });\n   478→\n   479→    // Timeout handler\n   480→    const timeout = effectiveTimeoutMs > 0\n   481→      ? setTimeout(() => {\n   482→          timedOut = true;\n   483→          const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   484→          if (info) {\n   485→            info.timedOut = true;\n   486→          }\n   487→          child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   488→\n   489→          // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n   490→          setTimeout(() => {\n   491→            if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n   492→              child.kill('SIGKILL');\n   493→            }\n   494→          }, 5000);\n   495→        }, effectiveTimeoutMs)\n   496→      : null;\n   497→\n   498→    // Abort signal handler\n   499→    const onAbort = () => {\n   500→      interrupted = true;\n   501→      const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   502→      if (info) {\n   503→        info.interrupted = true;\n   504→      }\n   505→      child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   506→\n   507→      // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n   508→      setTimeout(() => {\n   509→        if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n   510→          child.kill('SIGKILL');\n   511→        }\n   512→      }, 5000);\n   513→    };\n   514→\n   515→    if (signal) {\n   516→      signal.addEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n   517→    }\n   518→\n   519→    // Heartbeat setup\n   520→    if (enableHeartbeat && typeof hooks.onHeartbeat === 'function') {\n   521→      heartbeatManager.start({\n   522→        callback: () => {\n   523→          const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   524→          hooks.onHeartbeat({\n   525→            elapsedMs,\n   526→            stdoutBytes,\n   527→            status: 'running'\n   528→          });\n   529→        },\n   530→        intervalMs: effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs,\n   531→        thresholdMs: effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs\n   532→      });\n   533→    }\n   534→\n   535→    // Cleanup function\n   536→    function cleanup() {\n   537→      if (timeout) {\n   538→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   539→      }\n   540→      heartbeatManager.stop();\n   541→      sessionStore.clearActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   542→      if (signal) {\n   543→        signal.removeEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n   544→      }\n   545→    }\n   546→\n   547→    // Handle process close\n   548→    child.on('close', (code) => {\n   549→      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   550→\n   551→      // Check interrupted/timedOut flags from session store (may be set by interruptAiCli)\n   552→      const storedInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   553→      if (storedInfo) {\n   554→        if (storedInfo.interrupted) {\n   555→          interrupted = true;\n   556→        }\n   557→        if (storedInfo.timedOut) {\n   558→          timedOut = true;\n   559→        }\n   560→      }\n   561→\n   562→      cleanup();\n   563→\n   564→      logger.info(\n   565→        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000), sessionId },\n   566→        'AI CLI process closed'\n   567→      );\n   568→\n   569→      // Build output\n   570→      let output = stdout.trim();\n   571→\n   572→      if (interrupted) {\n   573→        output = output || '任务已被用户中断。';\n   574→      } else if (timedOut) {\n   575→        output = output || `任务执行超时（>${effectiveTimeoutMs}ms）。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`;\n   576→      } else if (code !== 0) {\n   577→        output = output || `AI CLI 退出码 ${code}。`;\n   578→        if (stderr.trim()) {\n   579→          output += `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}`;\n   580→        }\n   581→      }\n   582→\n   583→      // Record metrics (T-051)\n   584→      recordMetrics({\n   585→        elapsedMs,\n   586→        stdoutBytes,\n   587→        success: code === 0 && !interrupted && !timedOut,\n   588→        timedOut,\n   589→        interrupted\n   590→      });\n   591→\n   592→      resolve({\n   593→        output: output || 'AI CLI 未返回文本结果。',\n   594→        timedOut,\n   595→        interrupted,\n   596→        elapsedMs,\n   597→        exitCode: code,\n   598→        stderr: stderr.trim()\n   599→      });\n   600→    });\n   601→  });\n   602→}\n   603→\n   604→export function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {\n   605→  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   606→\n   607→  if (!processInfo) {\n   608→    return { ok: false, error: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n   609→  }\n   610→\n   611→  const { pid, childProcess } = processInfo;\n   612→\n   613→  try {\n   614→    // Mark as interrupted so close handler knows\n   615→    processInfo.interrupted = true;\n   616→\n   617→    // Send SIGTERM first\n   618→    childProcess.kill('SIGTERM');\n   619→\n   620→    // Schedule SIGKILL as backup\n   621→    setTimeout(() => {\n   622→      const stillRunning = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   623→      if (stillRunning) {\n   624→        try {\n   625→          childProcess.kill('SIGKILL');\n   626→        } catch {\n   627→          // Process already dead\n   628→        }\n   629→      }\n   630→    }, 5000);\n   631→\n   632→    logger.info({ pid, sessionId }, 'AI CLI process interrupted');\n   633→\n   634→    return { ok: true, pid };\n   635→  } catch (err) {\n   636→    return { ok: false, error: `中断失败: ${err.message}` };\n   637→  }\n   638→}\n   639→\n   640→export function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {\n   641→  return sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId) !== null;\n   642→}\n   643→\n   644→export function getActiveProcessInfo(sessionId) {\n   645→  const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   646→  if (!info) {\n   647→    return null;\n   648→  }\n   649→\n   650→  // Don't expose childProcess to external callers\n   651→  return {\n   652→    pid: info.pid,\n   653→    startedAt: info.startedAt,\n   654→    stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0,\n   655→    userId: info.userId\n   656→  };\n   657→}\n   658→\n   659→export function canInterruptAiCli(sessionId, requestUserId, isAdminFn) {\n   660→  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   661→\n   662→  if (!processInfo) {\n   663→    return { canInterrupt: false, reason: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n   664→  }\n   665→\n   666→  // Admin can always interrupt\n   667→  if (isAdminFn && isAdminFn(requestUserId)) {\n   668→    return { canInterrupt: true };\n   669→  }\n   670→\n   671→  // Task owner can interrupt\n   672→  const taskUserId = processInfo.userId;\n   673→  if (taskUserId && String(taskUserId) === String(requestUserId)) {\n   674→    return { canInterrupt: true };\n   675→  }\n   676→\n   677→  // Otherwise, permission denied\n   678→  return {\n   679→    canInterrupt: false,\n   680→    reason: '权限不足。只有任务发起者或管理员可以中断任务。'\n   681→  };\n   682→}\n   683→```\n   684→\n   685→### src/services/session-store.js (427 lines):\n   686→```javascript\n   687→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   688→\n   689→class SessionStore {\n   690→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   691→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n   692→  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n   693→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n   694→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   695→  // F-010: File search results state for pagination\n   696→  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n   697→  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking\n   698→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n   699→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n   700→  #commandHistoryBySessionKey = new Map();\n   701→  #envOverridesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   702→  #lastActivityBySessionKey = new Map();\n   703→  #userIdBySessionKey = new Map();\n   704→  #sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey = new Map();\n   705→  // F-015: AI CLI Backend Switcher\n   706→  #currentBackendBySessionKey = new Map();\n   707→\n   708→  get(sessionKey) {\n   709→    if (!this.#messagesBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n   710→      this.#messagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n   711→    }\n   712→    return this.#messagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   713→  }\n   714→\n   715→  append(sessionKey, role, content) {\n   716→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n   717→    messages.push({ role, content });\n   718→\n   719→    const maxMessages = config.maxHistoryTurns * 2;\n   720→    if (messages.length > maxMessages) {\n   721→      messages.splice(0, messages.length - maxMessages);\n   722→    }\n   723→  }\n   724→\n   725→  clear(sessionKey) {\n   726→    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   727→    this.#commitsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   728→    // F-009: Clear cwd and output pages\n   729→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   730→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   731→    // F-010: Clear search results\n   732→    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   733→    // F-011: Clear active process\n   734→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   735→    // F-013: Clear session context data\n   736→    this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   737→    this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   738→    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   739→    this.#userIdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   740→    this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   741→    // F-015: Clear backend selection\n   742→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   743→  }\n   744→\n   745→  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel = 'unknown') {\n   746→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n   747→\n   748→    return [\n   749→      `你正在通过 ${channel} 渠道提供电脑助手服务。`,\n   750→      '请使用自然、简洁、可执行的表达。',\n   751→      '如果用户请求系统操作或截图，明确说明步骤与结果。',\n   752→      '当你产出本地文件（截图/文档）时，必须额外输出独立行：SEND_FILE:<绝对路径>。',\n   753→      '禁止仅输出 @image:xxx 或相对路径；路径必须是绝对路径（例如 /var/folders/... 或 /home/...）。',\n   754→      '以下是最近对话上下文：',\n   755→      ...messages.map((msg) => `${msg.role === 'user' ? '用户' : '助手'}: ${msg.content}`),\n   756→      '请继续回答最后一条用户消息。'\n   757→    ].join('\\n');\n   758→  }\n   759→  // ... other methods for commits, cwd, output, search results, active process, command history, env overrides, session tracking, etc.\n   760→\n   761→  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking methods\n   762→  getActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n   763→    return this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n   764→  }\n   765→\n   766→  setActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) {\n   767→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, {\n   768→      ...info,\n   769→      stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0\n   770→    });\n   771→  }\n   772→\n   773→  updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) {\n   774→    const info = this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   775→    if (info) {\n   776→      info.stdoutBytes = (info.stdoutBytes ?? 0) + bytes;\n   777→    }\n   778→  }\n   779→\n   780→  clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n   781→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   782→  }\n   783→\n   784→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager methods\n   785→  touchSession(sessionKey, userId) {\n   786→    const now = Date.now();\n   787→    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n   788→    if (userId !== undefined) {\n   789→      this.#userIdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, userId);\n   790→    }\n   791→    // Set creation time if this is a new session\n   792→    if (!this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n   793→      this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n   794→    }\n   795→  }\n   796→\n   797→  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) {\n   798→    const userId = this.#userIdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   799→    const createdAt = this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   800→    const lastActivityAt = this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   801→\n   802→    // Return null if session has no tracking data\n   803→    if (!createdAt && !lastActivityAt) {\n   804→      return null;\n   805→    }\n   806→\n   807→    return {\n   808→      sessionKey,\n   809→      userId: userId || null,\n   810→      cwd: this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null,\n   811→      envOverrides: { ...this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) } || {},\n   812→      commandCount: (this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || []).length,\n   813→      createdAt: createdAt || null,\n   814→      lastActivityAt: lastActivityAt || null,\n   815→      // F-015: Add backend information\n   816→      currentBackend: this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null\n   817→    };\n   818→  }\n   819→\n   820→  getAllSessionKeys() {\n   821→    // Return keys from sessions that have activity tracking\n   822→    return Array.from(this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.keys());\n   823→  }\n   824→\n   825→  getCurrentBackend(sessionKey) {\n   826→    return this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n   827→  }\n   828→\n   829→  setCurrentBackend(sessionKey, backendName) {\n   830→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, backendName);\n   831→  }\n   832→\n   833→  resetBackend(sessionKey) {\n   834→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   835→  }\n   836→}\n   837→\n   838→export const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n   839→export { SessionStore };\n   840→```\n   841→\n   842→### src/services/realtime-hub.js (35 lines):\n   843→```javascript\n   844→class RealtimeHub {\n   845→  #listenersBySession = new Map();\n   846→\n   847→  subscribe(sessionKey, listener) {\n   848→    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey) ?? new Set();\n   849→    listeners.add(listener);\n   850→    this.#listenersBySession.set(sessionKey, listeners);\n   851→\n   852→    return () => {\n   853→      const current = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n   854→      if (!current) {\n   855→        return;\n   856→      }\n   857→\n   858→      current.delete(listener);\n   859→      if (current.size === 0) {\n   860→        this.#listenersBySession.delete(sessionKey);\n   861→      }\n   862→    };\n   863→  }\n   864→\n   865→  publish(sessionKey, event) {\n   866→    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n   867→    if (!listeners || listeners.size === 0) {\n   868→      return;\n   869→    }\n   870→\n   871→    for (const listener of listeners) {\n   872→      listener(event);\n   873→    }\n   874→  }\n   875→}\n   876→\n   877→export const realtimeHub = new RealtimeHub();\n   878→```\n   879→\n   880→### src/routes/api-routes.js (106 lines):\n   881→```javascript\n   882→import { Router } from 'express';\n   883→import { buildSessionContext, chatWithSession, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\n   884→import { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\n   885→import { executeSystemCommand } from '../services/system-exec-service.js';\n   886→\n   887→function writeSseEvent(res, event, payload) {\n   888→  res.write(`event: ${event}\\n`);\n   889→  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n\\n`);\n   890→}\n   891→\n   892→export function createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }) {\n   893→  const router = Router();\n   894→\n   895→  router.get('/events', (req, res, next) => {\n   896→    try {\n   897→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.query;\n   898→      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   899→\n   900→      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');\n   901→      res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');\n   902→      res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');\n   903→      res.flushHeaders?.();\n   904→\n   905→      writeSseEvent(res, 'connected', {\n   906→        ok: true,\n   907→        channel: session.channel,\n   908→        sessionId: session.sessionId\n   909→      });\n   910→\n   911→      const unsubscribe = realtimeHub.subscribe(session.sessionKey, (event) => {\n   912→        writeSseEvent(res, event.type, event.payload);\n   913→      });\n   914→\n   915→      const heartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n   916→        res.write(': ping\\n\\n');\n   917→      }, 20000);\n   918→\n   919→      req.on('close', () => {\n   920→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   921→        unsubscribe();\n   922→      });\n   923→    } catch (error) {\n   924→      next(error);\n   925→    }\n   926→  });\n   927→\n   928→  router.post('/chat', async (req, res, next) => {\n   929→    try {\n   930→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, message } = req.body ?? {};\n   931→      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   932→\n   933→      const reply = await chatWithSession({\n   934→        channel,\n   935→        sessionId,\n   936→        message,\n   937→        realtimeHooks: {\n   938→          onStatus: (payload) => {\n   939→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'status', payload });\n   940→          },\n   941→          onAssistantChunk: (payload) => {\n   942→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_chunk', payload });\n   943→          },\n   944→          onAssistantDone: (payload) => {\n   945→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_done', payload });\n   946→          }\n   947→        }\n   948→      });\n   949→\n   950→      res.json({ ok: true, reply });\n   951→    } catch (error) {\n   952→      next(error);\n   953→    }\n   954→  });\n   955→\n   956→  router.post('/chat/reset', async (req, res, next) => {\n   957→    try {\n   958→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.body ?? {};\n   959→      resetSession({ channel, sessionId });\n   960→      res.json({ ok: true });\n   961→    } catch (error) {\n   962→      next(error);\n   963→    }\n   964→  });\n   965→\n   966→  return router;\n   967→}\n   968→```\n   969→\n   970→### src/http/server.js (25 lines):\n   971→```javascript\n   972→import express from 'express';\n   973→import { createApiRouter } from '../routes/api-routes.js';\n   974→import { realtimeHub } from '../services/realtime-hub.js';\n   975→\n   976→export function createHttpServer({ logger }) {\n   977→  const app = express();\n   978→\n   979→  app.use(express.json({ limit: '2mb' }));\n   980→\n   981→  app.get('/healthz', (_req, res) => {\n   982→    res.json({ ok: true });\n   983→  });\n   984→\n   985→  app.use('/api', createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }));\n   986→  app.use(express.static('public'));\n   987→\n   988→  app.use((error, _req, res, _next) => {\n   989→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   990→    logger.error({ err: message }, 'HTTP request failed');\n   991→    res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: message });\n   992→  });\n   993→\n   994→  return app;\n   995→}\n   996→```\n   997→\n   998→### src/bot/telegram.js (partial - key sections related to chat handling):\n   999→```javascript\n  1000→// Key parts for context\n  1001→\n  1002→function buildSessionId(ctx) {\n  1003→  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n  1004→}\n  1005→\n  1006→// Bot uses ai-cli-service for execution:\n  1007→const result = await executeAiCli({\n  1008→  sessionId,\n  1009→  prompt,\n  1010→  hooks: {\n  1011→    onChunk: (text) => {\n  1012→      streamPublisher.push(text);\n  1013→    },\n  1014→    onHeartbeat: config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat ? (info) => {\n  1015→      // Send/update heartbeat progress message\n  1016→      const elapsedSec = Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000);\n  1017→      const progressText = `⏳ 任务执行中... (${elapsedSec}s, ${Math.floor(info.stdoutBytes / 1024)}KB)`;\n  1018→\n  1019→      // Don't await - fire and forget\n  1020→      if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n  1021→        ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id, undefined, progressText)\n  1022→          .catch(() => {});\n  1023→      } else {\n  1024→        ctx.reply(progressText)\n  1025→          .then((msg) => { lastHeartbeatMsg = msg; })\n  1026→          .catch(() => {});\n  1027→      }\n  1028→    } : undefined,\n  1029→    onStatus: (status) => {\n  1030→      if (status === 'running') {\n  1031→        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n  1032→      }\n  1033→    }\n  1034→  }\n  1035→});\n  1036→\n  1037→// Session key format: `telegram:${sessionId}`\n  1038→const sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n  1039→\n  1040→// Append user message to session history\n  1041→sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', ctx.message.text);\n  1042→\n  1043→// Append assistant reply to session history\n  1044→sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', result.output);\n  1045→```\n  1046→\n  1047→---\n  1048→\n  1049→## Section 5 — Integration Points\n  1050→\n  1051→### Current Flow:\n  1052→\n  1053→**Web Path:**\n  1054→1. POST /api/chat with message\n  1055→2. buildSessionContext() → sessionKey = \"web:<sessionId>\"\n  1056→3. chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() (via adapter)\n  1057→4. Uses realtimeHub.publish() for SSE\n  1058→\n  1059→**Telegram Path:**\n  1060→1. bot.on('text') receives message\n  1061→2. buildSessionId() → uses ctx.chat.id\n  1062→3. sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\"\n  1063→4. executeAiCli() directly\n  1064→5. Messages appended to sessionStore using sessionKey\n  1065→\n  1066→### Key Problem:\n  1067→- Web and Telegram use different execution engines (codebuddy vs ai-cli)\n  1068→- Session keys are isolated per channel (web:123 vs telegram:123)\n  1069→- No cross-channel message synchronization\n  1070→\n  1071→---\n  1072→\n  1073→## Section 6 — Data Flow Diagram\n  1074→\n  1075→```\n  1076→Web Client\n  1077→  │ POST /api/chat\n  1078→  ▼\n  1079→api-routes.js → chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() → sessionKey=\"web:id\"\n  1080→                                            │\n  1081→                                            ▼\n  1082→                                    session-store (isolated)\n  1083→\n  1084→Telegram Bot\n  1085→  │ on('text')\n  1086→  ▼\n  1087→telegram.js → executeAiCli() → sessionKey=\"telegram:id\"\n  1088→                            │\n  1089→                            ▼\n  1090→                        session-store (isolated)\n  1091→```\n  1092→\n  1093→### Target Flow:\n  1094→\n  1095→```\n  1096→Web Client          Telegram Bot\n  1097→  │                      │\n  1098→  ▼                      │\n  1099→Session Key = telegram:<chatId> (bound)\n  1100→  │                      │\n  1101→  ├──────────────────────┤\n  1102→  │                      │\n  1103→  ▼                      ▼\n  1104→executeAiCli()    executeAiCli()\n  1105→  │                      │\n  1106→  └──────────────────────┘\n  1107→              │\n  1108→              ▼\n  1109→      session-store shared\n  1110→              │\n  1111→              ▼\n  1112→      realtimeHub.publish()\n  1113→              │\n  1114→              ▼\n  1115→      Both clients receive events\n  1116→```\n  1117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_0a68ab29f41c4d6b90dd4982","session_id":"94710a11-4ada-4b2b-b382-cda110153e6d","uuid":"fde07f16-eda8-4512-a41c-091758b89f01","timestamp":"2026-03-22T01:58:10.983Z"}
